						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Kasumi wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You check 15 points for collision if your character is 16 pixels wide? (You already checked one, of course)</div>
<br />
<br />Well you wouldn't check all 15 points individually.  Instead you'd just take the "highest" point that has an X position that puts it underneath the character.
<br />
<br />This is easier with linear slopes.  If you have tokumaru's slope system where each column can have its own height, then yeah it's not very practical.</div>

